Airport database

As of January 2012, the OpenFlights Airports Database contains 6977 airports spanning the globe, as shown in the map above. Each entry contains the following information:
 0 Airport ID 	Unique OpenFlights identifier for this airport.
 1 Name 	Name of airport. May or may not contain the City name.
 2 City 	Main city served by airport. May be spelled differently from Name.
 3 Country 	Country or territory where airport is located.
 4 IATA/FAA 	3-letter FAA code, for airports located in Country "United States of America" OR 3-letter IATA code, for all other airports OR Blank if not assigned.
 7 ICAO 	4-letter ICAO code OR Blank if not assigned.
 9 Latitude 	Decimal degrees, usually to six significant digits. Negative is South, positive is North.
10  Longitude 	Decimal degrees, usually to six significant digits. Negative is West, positive is East.
11 Altitude 	In feet.
12 Timezone 	Hours offset from UTC. Fractional hours are expressed as decimals, eg. India is 5.5.
13 DST 	Daylight savings time. One of E (Europe), A (US/Canada), S (South America), O (Australia), Z (New Zealand), N (None) or U (Unknown). See also: Help: Time
14 Tz database time zone 	Timezone in "tz" (Olson) format, eg. "America/Los_Angeles". 
